[
    {
        "index": 1,
        "start_time": 6965,
        "end_time": 12590,
        "text": "Trillions of bacteria, viruses, and fungi\nlive on or inside of us,"
    },
    {
        "index": 2,
        "start_time": 12590,
        "end_time": 15389,
        "text": "and maintaining a good, balanced \nrelationship with them"
    },
    {
        "index": 3,
        "start_time": 15389,
        "end_time": 17450,
        "text": "is to our advantage."
    },
    {
        "index": 4,
        "start_time": 17450,
        "end_time": 20270,
        "text": "Together, they form the gut microbiome,"
    },
    {
        "index": 5,
        "start_time": 20270,
        "end_time": 24880,
        "text": "a rich ecosystem that performs a variety\nof functions in our bodies."
    },
    {
        "index": 6,
        "start_time": 24880,
        "end_time": 28771,
        "text": "The bacteria in our guts\ncan break down food the body can&#39;t digest,"
    },
    {
        "index": 7,
        "start_time": 28771,
        "end_time": 30621,
        "text": "produce important nutrients,"
    },
    {
        "index": 8,
        "start_time": 30621,
        "end_time": 32490,
        "text": "regulate the immune system,"
    },
    {
        "index": 9,
        "start_time": 32490,
        "end_time": 35951,
        "text": "and protect against harmful germs."
    },
    {
        "index": 10,
        "start_time": 35951,
        "end_time": 37560,
        "text": "We don&#39;t yet have the blueprint"
    },
    {
        "index": 11,
        "start_time": 37560,
        "end_time": 41751,
        "text": "for exactly which good bacteria \na robust gut needs,"
    },
    {
        "index": 12,
        "start_time": 41751,
        "end_time": 44672,
        "text": "but we do know that it&#39;s important\nfor a healthy microbiome"
    },
    {
        "index": 13,
        "start_time": 44672,
        "end_time": 47511,
        "text": "to have a variety of bacterial species."
    },
    {
        "index": 14,
        "start_time": 47511,
        "end_time": 49711,
        "text": "Many factors affect our microbiomes,"
    },
    {
        "index": 15,
        "start_time": 49711,
        "end_time": 51091,
        "text": "including our environment,"
    },
    {
        "index": 16,
        "start_time": 51091,
        "end_time": 53270,
        "text": "medications like antibiotics,"
    },
    {
        "index": 17,
        "start_time": 53270,
        "end_time": 57922,
        "text": "and even whether we were delivered\nby C-section or not."
    },
    {
        "index": 18,
        "start_time": 57922,
        "end_time": 61121,
        "text": "Diet, too, is emerging as one \nof the leading influences"
    },
    {
        "index": 19,
        "start_time": 61121,
        "end_time": 63611,
        "text": "on the health of our guts."
    },
    {
        "index": 20,
        "start_time": 63611,
        "end_time": 66021,
        "text": "And while we can&#39;t control all \nthese factors,"
    },
    {
        "index": 21,
        "start_time": 66021,
        "end_time": 68372,
        "text": "we can manipulate the balance\nof our microbes"
    },
    {
        "index": 22,
        "start_time": 68372,
        "end_time": 71712,
        "text": "by paying attention to what we eat."
    },
    {
        "index": 23,
        "start_time": 71712,
        "end_time": 77572,
        "text": "Dietary fiber from foods like fruits, \nvegetables, nuts, legumes, and whole grains"
    },
    {
        "index": 24,
        "start_time": 77572,
        "end_time": 81151,
        "text": "is the best fuel for gut bacteria."
    },
    {
        "index": 25,
        "start_time": 81151,
        "end_time": 83022,
        "text": "When bacteria digest fiber,"
    },
    {
        "index": 26,
        "start_time": 83022,
        "end_time": 87235,
        "text": "they produce short chain fatty acids\nthat nourish the gut barrier,"
    },
    {
        "index": 27,
        "start_time": 87235,
        "end_time": 90192,
        "text": "improve immune function,"
    },
    {
        "index": 28,
        "start_time": 90192,
        "end_time": 94716,
        "text": "and can help prevent inflammation,\nwhich reduces the risk of cancer."
    },
    {
        "index": 29,
        "start_time": 94716,
        "end_time": 96426,
        "text": "And the more fiber you ingest,"
    },
    {
        "index": 30,
        "start_time": 96426,
        "end_time": 100904,
        "text": "the more fiber-digesting bacteria\ncolonize your gut."
    },
    {
        "index": 31,
        "start_time": 100904,
        "end_time": 105123,
        "text": "In a recent study, scientists exchanged\nthe regular high-fiber diets"
    },
    {
        "index": 32,
        "start_time": 105123,
        "end_time": 107363,
        "text": "of a group of rural South Africans"
    },
    {
        "index": 33,
        "start_time": 107363,
        "end_time": 112624,
        "text": "with the high-fat, meat-heavy diets\nof a group of African-Americans."
    },
    {
        "index": 34,
        "start_time": 112624,
        "end_time": 117054,
        "text": "After just two weeks on the high-fat,\nlow-fiber, Western-style diet,"
    },
    {
        "index": 35,
        "start_time": 117054,
        "end_time": 120962,
        "text": "the rural African group showed\nincreased inflammation of the colon,"
    },
    {
        "index": 36,
        "start_time": 120962,
        "end_time": 123525,
        "text": "as well as a decrease of butyrate."
    },
    {
        "index": 37,
        "start_time": 123525,
        "end_time": 128163,
        "text": "That&#39;s a short chain fatty acid thought\nto lower risk of colon cancer."
    },
    {
        "index": 38,
        "start_time": 128163,
        "end_time": 131574,
        "text": "Meanwhile, the group that switched\nto a high-fiber, low-fat diet"
    },
    {
        "index": 39,
        "start_time": 131574,
        "end_time": 134943,
        "text": "had the opposite result."
    },
    {
        "index": 40,
        "start_time": 134943,
        "end_time": 140183,
        "text": "So what goes wrong with our gut bacteria \nwhen we eat low-fiber processed foods?"
    },
    {
        "index": 41,
        "start_time": 140183,
        "end_time": 144093,
        "text": "Lower fiber means less fuel\nfor the gut bacteria,"
    },
    {
        "index": 42,
        "start_time": 144093,
        "end_time": 147583,
        "text": "essentially starving them \nuntil they die off."
    },
    {
        "index": 43,
        "start_time": 147583,
        "end_time": 149804,
        "text": "This results in less diversity"
    },
    {
        "index": 44,
        "start_time": 149804,
        "end_time": 152074,
        "text": "and hungry bacteria."
    },
    {
        "index": 45,
        "start_time": 152074,
        "end_time": 156633,
        "text": "In fact, some can even start to feed\non the mucus lining."
    },
    {
        "index": 46,
        "start_time": 156633,
        "end_time": 161175,
        "text": "We also know that specific foods \ncan affect gut bacteria."
    },
    {
        "index": 47,
        "start_time": 161175,
        "end_time": 163345,
        "text": "In one recent microbiome study,"
    },
    {
        "index": 48,
        "start_time": 163345,
        "end_time": 164925,
        "text": "scientists found that fruits,"
    },
    {
        "index": 49,
        "start_time": 164925,
        "end_time": 165864,
        "text": "vegetables,"
    },
    {
        "index": 50,
        "start_time": 165864,
        "end_time": 166614,
        "text": "tea,"
    },
    {
        "index": 51,
        "start_time": 166614,
        "end_time": 167364,
        "text": "coffee,"
    },
    {
        "index": 52,
        "start_time": 167364,
        "end_time": 168263,
        "text": "red wine,"
    },
    {
        "index": 53,
        "start_time": 168263,
        "end_time": 169284,
        "text": "and dark chocolate"
    },
    {
        "index": 54,
        "start_time": 169284,
        "end_time": 173154,
        "text": "were correlated with \nincreased bacterial diversity."
    },
    {
        "index": 55,
        "start_time": 173154,
        "end_time": 175945,
        "text": "These foods contain polyphenols,"
    },
    {
        "index": 56,
        "start_time": 175945,
        "end_time": 180114,
        "text": "which are naturally occurring \nantioxidant compounds."
    },
    {
        "index": 57,
        "start_time": 180114,
        "end_time": 181155,
        "text": "On the other hand,"
    },
    {
        "index": 58,
        "start_time": 181155,
        "end_time": 182815,
        "text": "foods high in dairy fat,"
    },
    {
        "index": 59,
        "start_time": 182815,
        "end_time": 185504,
        "text": "like whole milk, and sugar-sweetened sodas"
    },
    {
        "index": 60,
        "start_time": 185504,
        "end_time": 188564,
        "text": "were correlated with decreased diversity."
    },
    {
        "index": 61,
        "start_time": 188564,
        "end_time": 191055,
        "text": "How food is prepared also matters."
    },
    {
        "index": 62,
        "start_time": 191055,
        "end_time": 194524,
        "text": "Minimally processed, fresh foods\ngenerally have more fiber"
    },
    {
        "index": 63,
        "start_time": 194524,
        "end_time": 196745,
        "text": "and provide better fuel."
    },
    {
        "index": 64,
        "start_time": 196745,
        "end_time": 197836,
        "text": "So lightly steamed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 65,
        "start_time": 197836,
        "end_time": 198598,
        "text": "saut\u00e9ed,"
    },
    {
        "index": 66,
        "start_time": 198598,
        "end_time": 199675,
        "text": "or raw vegetables"
    },
    {
        "index": 67,
        "start_time": 199675,
        "end_time": 203255,
        "text": "are typically more beneficial\nthan fried dishes."
    },
    {
        "index": 68,
        "start_time": 203255,
        "end_time": 207785,
        "text": "There are also ways of preparing food\nthat can actually introduce good bacteria,"
    },
    {
        "index": 69,
        "start_time": 207785,
        "end_time": 211454,
        "text": "also known as probiotics,\ninto your gut."
    },
    {
        "index": 70,
        "start_time": 211454,
        "end_time": 215355,
        "text": "Fermented foods are teeming\nwith helpful probiotic bacteria,"
    },
    {
        "index": 71,
        "start_time": 215355,
        "end_time": 216564,
        "text": "like lactobacillus"
    },
    {
        "index": 72,
        "start_time": 216564,
        "end_time": 218545,
        "text": "and bifidobacteria."
    },
    {
        "index": 73,
        "start_time": 218545,
        "end_time": 220965,
        "text": "Originally used as a way \nof preserving foods"
    },
    {
        "index": 74,
        "start_time": 220965,
        "end_time": 223387,
        "text": "before the invention of refrigeration,"
    },
    {
        "index": 75,
        "start_time": 223387,
        "end_time": 227135,
        "text": "fermentation remains a traditional\npractice all over the world."
    },
    {
        "index": 76,
        "start_time": 227135,
        "end_time": 228316,
        "text": "Foods like kimchi,"
    },
    {
        "index": 77,
        "start_time": 228316,
        "end_time": 229156,
        "text": "sauerkraut,"
    },
    {
        "index": 78,
        "start_time": 229156,
        "end_time": 230095,
        "text": "tempeh,"
    },
    {
        "index": 79,
        "start_time": 230095,
        "end_time": 231026,
        "text": "and kombucha"
    },
    {
        "index": 80,
        "start_time": 231026,
        "end_time": 234196,
        "text": "provide variety and vitality\nto our diets."
    },
    {
        "index": 81,
        "start_time": 234196,
        "end_time": 238766,
        "text": "Yogurt is another fermented food that can\nintroduce helpful bacteria into our guts."
    },
    {
        "index": 82,
        "start_time": 238766,
        "end_time": 242877,
        "text": "That doesn&#39;t necessarily mean that\nall yogurt is good for us, though."
    },
    {
        "index": 83,
        "start_time": 242877,
        "end_time": 245226,
        "text": "Brands with too much sugar\nand not enough bacteria"
    },
    {
        "index": 84,
        "start_time": 245226,
        "end_time": 247527,
        "text": "may not actually help."
    },
    {
        "index": 85,
        "start_time": 247527,
        "end_time": 249197,
        "text": "These are just general guidelines."
    },
    {
        "index": 86,
        "start_time": 249197,
        "end_time": 251816,
        "text": "More research is needed before \nwe fully understand"
    },
    {
        "index": 87,
        "start_time": 251816,
        "end_time": 256687,
        "text": "exactly how any of these foods\ninteract with our microbiomes."
    },
    {
        "index": 88,
        "start_time": 256687,
        "end_time": 258253,
        "text": "We see positive correlations,"
    },
    {
        "index": 89,
        "start_time": 258253,
        "end_time": 263397,
        "text": "but the insides of our guts are difficult\nplaces to make direct observations."
    },
    {
        "index": 90,
        "start_time": 263397,
        "end_time": 265258,
        "text": "For instance, we don&#39;t currently know"
    },
    {
        "index": 91,
        "start_time": 265258,
        "end_time": 268907,
        "text": "whether these foods are directly\nresponsible for the changes in diversity,"
    },
    {
        "index": 92,
        "start_time": 268907,
        "end_time": 272381,
        "text": "or if something more complicated\nis happening."
    },
    {
        "index": 93,
        "start_time": 272381,
        "end_time": 276338,
        "text": "While we&#39;re only beginning to explore\nthe vast wilderness inside our guts,"
    },
    {
        "index": 94,
        "start_time": 276338,
        "end_time": 282167,
        "text": "we already have a glimpse of how crucial\nour microbiomes are for digestive health."
    },
    {
        "index": 95,
        "start_time": 282167,
        "end_time": 287817,
        "text": "The great news is we have the power\nto fire up the bacteria in our bellies."
    },
    {
        "index": 96,
        "start_time": 287817,
        "end_time": 289017,
        "text": "Fill up on fibers,"
    },
    {
        "index": 97,
        "start_time": 289017,
        "end_time": 290668,
        "text": "fresh and fermented foods,"
    },
    {
        "index": 98,
        "start_time": 290668,
        "end_time": 293677,
        "text": "and you can trust your gut\nto keep you going strong."
    }
]